Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Halve the @Ciabatta{2} and lay them, cut-side up, onto a #baking tray{}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Spread the garlic over the cut sides of the ciabatta. Drizzle over a little @olive oil{} and set aside.

Cut the @Medium Tomato{2} into 1cm chunks. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}. Halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board, then chop into 2cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, lay the @Serrano Ham{2} in the pan and fry until crisp, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Once crispy, transfer to a #plate{} covered in #kitchen paper{}. Set aside.

Pop the frying pan back onto medium-high heat with a drizzle more @olive oil{} if needed. Once hot, add the onion and stir-fry until softened, ~{6-8%minutes}. Add the @Sugar{1}, @Water{1}(see pantry for amount) and half the @Balsamic Vinegar{12}ml, then lower the heat and simmer until caramelised, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

> See pantry for sugar and water amounts.

Meanwhile, bake the ciabatta on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. While the ciabatta bakes, add the @Olive Oil{for the Dressing} and remaining balsamic to a large #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together well. Just before serving, add the tomatoes, avocado and @Wild Rocket{40} to the dressing. Toss to coat.

When everything's ready, share the toasted ciabatta between your plates. Spoon over the caramelised onions and top with a handful of salad. Drain the @Mozzarella{1}, then tear it into small pieces and place on top. Snap the Serrano ham into shards and scatter over the bruschetta. Serve any remaining salad alongside.

Enjoy!